quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  3,133,"And rush towards forgiveness from your Lord, and towards a Paradise that can hold all the heavens and the earth in its width – prepared for the pious."
  3,134,"Those who spend in Allah’s cause, in happiness and in grief, and who control their anger and are forgiving towards mankind; and the righteous are the beloved of Allah."
  3,135,"And those who, when they commit an immoral act or wrong themselves, remember Allah and seek forgiveness of their sins – and who forgives sins except Allah? And those who do not purposely become stubborn regarding what they did."
  3,136,"For such the reward is forgiveness from their Lord, and Gardens beneath which rivers flow – abiding in it forever; what an excellent reward for the performers (of good deeds)!"
  3,137,"Some traditions have been tried before you – therefore travel in the land and see what sort of fate befell those who denied."
  3,138,"This is an explanation for mankind, a guidance and an advice to the pious."
  3,139,"And do not be negligent nor grieve – it is you who will be victorious if you are believers."
  3,140,"If you have been struck by some misfortune, so they (the disbelievers) too have been struck earlier with the same misfortune; these are the days in which We have allotted turns to people; and so that Allah may make known the believers and may bestow martyrdom to some of you; and Allah does not befriend the unjust."
